Title: One Minute at a Time
Credit: Written by
Author: Yael Persky Luvovski
Source: University Multimedia Vibe-Coding Assignment (EX06)
Draft date: 2026-07-03

= A 60-second animated short about a student who learns to manage her time, told across three scenes.

INT. MAYA'S DORM ROOM - MORNING

An alarm clock SCREAMS. MAYA (20, wavy hair escaping a messy bun, oversized mustard hoodie) jolts upright in bed, eyes wide with panic.

The room is chaos: books towering off-balance, papers drifting off a cluttered desk, a wall clock whose hands spin unnaturally fast.

MAYA
(groggy, panicked)
No, no, no -- not again!

She scrambles out of bed, knocks a coffee mug off the nightstand. It shatters. She doesn't stop to look.

Maya trips over her own backpack, catches herself on the doorframe.

THROUGH THE WINDOW, the campus bus pulls away without her.

MAYA (CONT'D)
(breathless, defeated)
Missed it. Again.

She collapses face-down onto the desk, arms sprawled across scattered papers.

CLOSE ON the clock. Its hands keep spinning, indifferent.

INT. MAYA'S DORM ROOM - CONTINUOUS

Maya's phone GLOWS on the desk beside her face. She lifts her head, squinting at it.

She taps the screen. The TIMEWISE app icon blooms open -- a soft, warm sparkle animation, purple-to-teal gradient light spilling across her face.

A calendar and a checklist assemble themselves on screen in friendly, rounded cards.

MAYA (CONT'D)
(quietly, surprised)
Huh. Okay... let's try this.

She sits up, taps the first item on the checklist. It gets a satisfying little check-mark "ding."

Her exhausted expression softens into curiosity, then something close to hope.

EXT. CAMPUS - DAY

Sunlight. Maya walks across the quad with an easy, confident stride, glancing at TimeWise on her phone, checking off another task as she walks.

She spots her friend JORDAN waiting by the classroom door and breaks into a grin.

MAYA (CONT'D)
(to Jordan, cheerful)
Early for once!

They high-five. Maya slides into her seat, calm, organized, on time.

CLOSE ON her phone screen: every task for the day is checked off. The TIMEWISE logo settles gently beside the words:

SUPERIMPOSE: "ONE MINUTE AT A TIME"

FADE OUT.
